      <body>
         <head>To <persName>
                    <ptr target="/persons/pers1420.xml"/>George Merryweather</persName>
                <note place="foot" n="1">This letter initiates <persName>
                        <ptr target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>John Wesley</persName>'s correspondence
               with <persName>
                        <ptr target="/persons/pers1420.xml"/>George Merryweather</persName>, a
               merchant of <placeName>Yarm</placeName> whom <persName>
                        <ptr target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>Wesley</persName> had known since at least
                  <date when="1748">1748</date> when <persName>
                        <ptr target="/persons/pers1420.xml"/>Merryweather</persName> invited <persName>
                        <ptr target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>Wesley</persName> to preach there; see Vickers, Dictionary,
            229–30.</note>
            </head>
         <opener>
                <placeName>London</placeName>
                <lb/>
                <date when="1758-01-16">January 16, 1758</date>
                <lb/>
                <lb/>
            <salute>My Dear Brother,</salute>
         </opener>
         <p>If the work of God does so increase at <placeName>Yarm</placeName>, we must not let the
            opportunity slip. Therefore let the <seg ana="itinerancy">travelling preacher</seg> be there either every Sunday
            evening, or at least every other Sunday. </p>
         <p>No person must be allowed to preach or exhort among our people whose life is not holy
            and unblameable, nor any who asserts anything contrary to the gospel which we have
               received<note place="foot" n="2">See <index indexName="biblical">
                  <term cRef="Gal1:8–9">Gal. 1:8–9</term>
               </index>.</note>. And if he does not own his fault and amend it, he cannot be a
            leader any longer. </p>
         <closer>Peace be with you all. I am,<lb/>
            <signed>Your affectionate brother,<lb/>
                    <persName>J. Wesley</persName>
                </signed>
            </closer>
      </body>
   </text>
